# Robyn Exercise: Semi-Automated MMM with Meta's Package

## What You'll Build

A Marketing Mix Model using [Meta Robyn](https://robyn.ai) — a widely-used open-source MMM package that automates much of the model selection process using multi-objective optimization (Nevergrad). By the end you will have:

- A Pareto frontier of candidate models to choose from
- Estimated ROI for 4 media channels with confidence ranges
- Response curves and a budget reallocation recommendation
- Experience with Robyn's distinctive "model selection" workflow

**Estimated time:** 1.5–3 hours (Robyn is faster to set up than Meridian)

---

## Meridian vs. Robyn: Key Differences

| | Meridian | Robyn |
|---|---|---|
| Language | Python | R (this exercise) |
| Framework | Bayesian (MCMC) | Frequentist + Nevergrad optimization |
| Model selection | Single model with posteriors | Pareto frontier of many models |
| Adstock types | Geometric | Geometric + Weibull |
| Uncertainty | Credible intervals | Pareto frontier spread |
| Fit time | Slower (MCMC) | Faster (optimization) |

